 {"id":"bd-j9jo3.7.3","title":"robot-redesign/registry: define registry-backed metadata for machine consumers and summary views","description":"Define the additional registry-backed metadata needed by machine consumers, summary views, and future transport integrations. This task exists because once a registry exists, ntm should use it to make machine integration more ergonomic instead of stopping at help text, especially around how consumers discover limits, drill-down paths, and compression semantics.","design":"The metadata may include stable section descriptions, consumer guidance, field-level or section-level summary hints, transport availability markers, replacement or removal markers when surfaces change, boundedness metadata such as default limits, truncation behavior, pagination support, recommended follow-up inspect surfaces, structured action-handoff hints, request or correlation semantics, whether a surface emits or accepts idempotency material, supported attention-state operations such as acknowledge or snooze or pin, and explainability metadata such as diagnostic entry points, explanation-handle semantics, evidence-summary availability, and aggregation or resurfacing cues for compacted attention items. The key is to expose enough structured meaning that agents and transport layers do less guesswork. This task should remain pragmatic: only encode metadata that improves real consumers.","acceptance_criteria":"This task is complete when downstream machine consumers and summary generators can obtain useful structured metadata from the registry, including how to interpret bounded or compressed views, how to correlate requests and outcomes, and how operator attention state changes what is shown, hidden, or force-prioritized.","notes":"This is one of the cleaner ways to steal ideas from vibe_cockpit's registry discipline without overbuilding a framework.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":150,"created_at":"2026-03-21T23:38:22.378960630Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-26T21:17:28.903416950Z","closed_at":"2026-03-26T21:17:28.903163135Z","close_reason":"Implemented registry-backed metadata for machine consumers: ConsumerGuidance, BoundednessInfo, FollowUpInfo, ActionHandoffInfo, RequestSemantics, AttentionOpsInfo, ExplainabilityInfo, LifecycleInfo types; section-level metadata; populated metadata for key surfaces (status, snapshot, attention, terse, capabilities, inspect-*, beads-list, triage, etc.) and all sections; added clone functions and tests","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["consumers","registry","robot-redesign"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.7.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.10","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:23:33.580146527Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.7.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.11","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:29:50.132806332Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.7.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.12","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:47:59.577804212Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.7.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.6","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:57:25.327784097Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.7.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.7","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:02:36.768707006Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.7.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.8","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:10:27.620062865Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.7.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.9","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:17:52.363446158Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.7.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.7","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:38:22.378960630Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.7.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.7.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:38:35.158585130Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.7.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.7.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:38:35.637453438Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":337,"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.7.3","author":"ubuntu","text":"Watch-semantics follow-up: machine-consumer metadata should include stream or watch availability, event taxonomy hints, selector or filter affordances, heartbeat expectations, and enough metadata that an agent can distinguish idle, filtered, and degraded long-lived consumption without trial-and-error.","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:49:03Z"},{"id":367,"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.7.3","author":"codex","text":"Plan-space refinement: this metadata bead now effectively feeds dashboard parity, schema goldens, discovery tests, and docs. Keep the summary-hint, boundedness, follow-up inspect, and explanation metadata concrete enough that human summary views and machine consumers can derive behavior from one source instead of hardcoding a second summary layer.","created_at":"2026-03-26T19:45:28Z"},{"id":373,"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.7.3","author":"codex","text":"Priority raised to P1 after graph audit: this metadata bead now gates dashboard parity, schema goldens, discovery tests, and docs, so leaving it at P2 would understate its actual user-facing importance.","created_at":"2026-03-26T19:59:14Z"}]}
 {"id":"bd-j9jo3.8","title":"robot-redesign/parity: REST, dashboard, and transport parity","description":"Repoint REST handlers, dashboard summaries, and transport-specific attention streams at the same projection and contract layer used by robot CLI surfaces. This epic exists so the redesign does not improve CLI JSON while leaving server and dashboard code to rot on older assembly paths.","design":"Parity here means semantic parity, not byte-for-byte identical payloads. All consumers should agree on section names, degraded-state meaning, cursor semantics, and next-action cues even when the final presentation differs by transport.\\n\\nThe long-term payoff is that future changes land once in the projection/registry layer instead of being copied into multiple stacks.","acceptance_criteria":"This epic is complete when REST, SSE, WebSocket, dashboard markdown, and other summary renderers consume the same normalized contract and stop carrying divergent logic.","notes":"Transport parity is not optional cleanup. It is part of making the robot contract trustworthy.","status":"open","priority":4,"issue_type":"epic","estimated_minutes":240,"created_at":"2026-03-21T23:32:12.693053559Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-22T00:10:20.760605701Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["parity","robot-redesign"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.8","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:32:12.693053559Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":320,"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.8","author":"ubuntu","text":"Future self: if one transport has a field or section nobody else has, ask whether it belongs in the shared projection model instead.","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:32:13Z"}]}
 {"id":"bd-j9jo3.8.1","title":"robot-redesign/parity: repoint REST handlers at the shared projection model","description":"Refactor REST handlers to serve the same shared runtime sections and semantics as the CLI robot surfaces. This task exists because transport parity should come from shared projection logic, not from parallel implementations that happen to look similar for a while.","design":"The work should make server handlers thin adapters over the same projection-backed surfaces used by CLI robot commands. It should also ensure REST consumers get the same freshness, schema, degraded-state, action-handoff, request-correlation or idempotency, operator-attention-state, explainability, and recoverable-error semantics as CLI consumers, including aggregated attention behavior, diagnostic drill-down access, and evidence references where the contract exposes them. The purpose is eliminating parallel truth, not merely exposing more endpoints.","acceptance_criteria":"This task is complete when REST handlers clearly project from the shared model and surface contracts no longer depend on transport-specific assembly logic, including for correlated actuation outcomes, compacted attention semantics, and durable operator overrides.","notes":"Paritizing REST early prevents the redesign from calcifying into a CLI-only architecture that later has to be copied again.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":180,"created_at":"2026-03-21T23:38:23.380385406Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-26T21:17:52.343564039Z","closed_at":"2026-03-26T21:17:52.343334370Z","close_reason":"Completed REST parity: added thin adapter handlers for robot surfaces (health, snapshot, digest, attention, dashboard, terse, triage, plan, graph, activity, alerts) and GetDigest function for API parity","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["parity","rest","robot-redesign"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.8.1","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.10","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:23:34.175138941Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.8.1","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.11","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:29:50.816308766Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.8.1","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.7","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:02:37.375221190Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.8.1","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.9","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:17:52.996057802Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.8.1","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:40:08.743121964Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.8.1","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:40:09.262803418Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.8.1","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:40:09.830560420Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.8.1","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:40:10.394501216Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.8.1","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.6","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:48:03.393778099Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.8.1","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.7","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:10:36.264043028Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.8.1","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.7.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:40:10.896632716Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.8.1","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.8","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:38:23.380385406Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
-{"id":"bd-j9jo3.8.2","title":"robot-redesign/parity: align dashboard and alternate renderers with snapshot and attention sections","description":"Align the TUI dashboard and alternate renderer flows with the same snapshot and attention section model. This task exists because the dashboard should share the robot mental model rather than presenting a separate worldview that only coincidentally overlaps.","design":"The work should decide how dashboard screens, terse output, markdown output, and TOON output consume shared sections, summary metadata, and diagnostics or explainability affordances. It should explicitly preserve legitimate UI-specific affordances while preventing them from becoming a separate semantic branch, so human operators can answer why questions without diverging from machine-consumable semantics.\n\nThe result should be that snapshot and attention are conceptually recognizable everywhere.","acceptance_criteria":"This task is complete when dashboard and alternate renderer experiences clearly reuse the shared section model and no longer depend on divergent state assembly paths.","notes":"Parity here improves operator ergonomics for both human and machine users, because it makes the product's mental model consistent.","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":180,"created_at":"2026-03-21T23:38:24.335450017Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-26T21:41:53.852904634Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["dashboard","parity","robot-redesign"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.8.2","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:40:11.434476151Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.8.2","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:40:11.967287453Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.8.2","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.5","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:40:12.536297631Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.8.2","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.7","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:10:36.951777963Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.8.2","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.7.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-26T19:44:52.669593523Z","created_by":"codex","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.8.2","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.8","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:38:24.335450017Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":368,"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.8.2","author":"codex","text":"Plan-space refinement: 8.2 now waits on 7.3 because dashboard and alternate renderer parity should consume registry-backed summary metadata and drill-down hints, not invent another UI-local semantic layer. Preserve UI-specific affordances, but keep the meaning anchored in shared metadata.","created_at":"2026-03-26T19:45:32Z"},{"id":375,"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.8.2","author":"codex","text":"Priority raised to P1 after plan-space audit: dashboard and alternate-renderer parity are a core operator experience, not a nice-to-have. Once 6.5 and 7.3 land, this should move immediately so human-facing views stop drifting from the shared robot semantics before validation freezes them.","created_at":"2026-03-26T21:08:25Z"}]}
-{"id":"bd-j9jo3.8.3","title":"robot-redesign/parity: align SSE and WebSocket behavior with durable attention semantics","description":"Align server-side streaming transports with the same durable attention semantics used elsewhere. This task exists because once attention and digest become restart-safe operator primitives, streaming transports must stop inventing their own event meanings.","design":"The work should ensure SSE and WebSocket streams honor the same cursor, replay, resync, degraded-state, request-correlation, idempotency, aggregation, cooldown, resurfacing, operator-attention-state, action-handoff, and recoverable-error semantics as CLI and REST consumers. It should also decide how stream initialization, backlog replay, and handoff to live updates behave when items are pinned, snoozed, acknowledged, muted, or manually escalated. This task is about semantic alignment, not merely plumbing bytes over a socket.","acceptance_criteria":"This task is complete when streaming transports can be treated as alternative delivery mechanisms for the same durable, deduplicated, operator-shaped, and request-correlated event product rather than as bespoke feeds.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":180,"created_at":"2026-03-21T23:38:25.318193079Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-26T21:14:48.789979612Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["parity","robot-redesign","streaming"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.8.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.10","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:23:34.759084751Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.8.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.11","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:29:51.524008109Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.8.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.12","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:48:00.515239538Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.8.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.7","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:02:37.977760883Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.8.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.9","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:17:53.634972268Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.8.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.3.5","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:36:35.335495935Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.8.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:40:13.032379944Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.8.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.6","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:23:44.380223071Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.8.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.7","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:30:03.926006101Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.8.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.8","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:48:08.573117873Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.8.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.8","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:38:25.318193079Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.8.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.8.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:38:36.107092492Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":338,"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.8.3","author":"ubuntu","text":"Watch-semantics follow-up: SSE and WebSocket parity now explicitly covers heartbeats, filtered subscriptions, replay-to-live handoff, liveness deadlines, backpressure or boundedness markers, and consistent meaning for quiet periods.","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:49:04Z"},{"id":355,"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.8.3","author":"ubuntu","text":"Sensitivity follow-up: SSE and WebSocket parity must prove that streaming and replay handoff preserve the same disclosure-control behavior as CLI and REST, including no-leak guarantees for safe previews and redaction markers.","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:37:24Z"},{"id":377,"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.8.3","author":"codex","text":"Priority raised to P1 after plan-space audit: streaming parity is a user-facing contract and a disclosure boundary, not secondary plumbing. Once 4.8 and 8.1 are done, SSE and WebSocket should converge before validation or docs treat the redesign as finished.","created_at":"2026-03-26T21:09:25Z"}]}
