 {"id":"bd-j9jo3.9.6","title":"robot-redesign/validation: build deterministic fixtures, fault-injection harness, and verbose test logging helpers","description":"Build the shared Go-based validation infrastructure that makes the rest of the redesign testable, benchmarkable, deterministic, and debuggable. This task exists because schema goldens, unit tests, integration tests, E2E coverage, and performance regressions will all be weaker and noisier if they each reinvent setup, fixture generation, and failure injection.","design":"The harness should provide deterministic fixture builders for tmux, session, process, coordination, quota, health, incident, cursor, request, outcome, operator-attention-state, and runtime-projection state; fault-injection helpers for degraded-source, duplicate-request, safe-retry, and partial-failure scenarios; SQLite seed builders; and shared assertion, logging, and measurement helpers that record scenario IDs, schema IDs, request IDs, idempotency keys, cursor values, source_health deltas, degraded features, incident IDs, operator-state transitions, suppression markers, resurfacing decisions, response diffs, payload sizes, error codes, remediation hints, diagnostic handles, evidence summaries, and other benchmark-relevant observations. All of this should stay within Go testing infrastructure: package-local _test.go code, reusable test helpers, and checked-in testdata/robot_redesign fixtures rather than ad hoc shell tooling.","acceptance_criteria":"This task is complete when downstream validation and benchmark tasks can run deterministically, inject realistic failure conditions, measure representative scenarios, and emit rich debugging context for retry-safe, attention-hygiene, and operator-control behavior without depending on live tmux state or external services except in explicitly gated E2E scenarios.","notes":"The harness must make tests more transparent, not more magical. Shared helpers should expose scenario structure and assertion diffs instead of swallowing them.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"ubuntu","estimated_minutes":210,"created_at":"2026-03-21T23:47:46.030223009Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-26T21:27:26.198359369Z","closed_at":"2026-03-26T21:27:26.198061642Z","close_reason":"Implemented deterministic fixture builders for sessions, agents, events, incidents, quotas, coordination, outcomes, and operator attention state; fault-injection helpers for degraded sources, duplicate requests, and partial failures; shared test recorder with observation logging; assertion helpers for cursors, payloads, schema fields, response diffs; benchmark measurement utilities; checked-in testdata/robot_redesign fixtures","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["harness","robot-redesign","validation"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.6","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.10","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:23:37.147238752Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.6","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.11","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:29:55.108799104Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.6","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:48:03.942966539Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.6","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:48:04.486590308Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.6","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.5","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:48:05.034788313Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.6","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.7","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:02:39.804971976Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.6","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.8","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-